OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJohnson faces two-day      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fgrilling at Covid inquiry  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Former Prime Minister Boris Johnson    
OL,6, will have a chance to defend his       
OL,7, handling of the pandemic in two days of
OL,8, questioning at the Covid inquiry.      
OL,10,FMr Johnson is expected to apologise to 
OL,11,Fthe inquiry and admit his government   
OL,12,Fmade mistakes during the pandemic.     
OL,14,FBut sources close to Mr Johnson have   
OL,15,Ftold the BBC he will argue he got big  
OL,16,Fcalls right that saved lives.          
OL,18,FThe inquiry has seen heavy criticism of
OL,19,FMr Johnson by former colleagues who    
OL,20,Fworked with him when Covid-19 struck.  
